      "`r.life(.5, 3)` is a little bit weird because people tend to think in terms of half-lives and you can always represent it in terms of a half life. For example `r.life(.75, 3)` is really equivalent to `r.half_life(ln(.5) / ln(.75), 3)` users can always just convert if they want to."
